You are generating a synthetic dataset of student emails to a university lecturer.
Goal: produce realistic, diverse, and label-consistent emails for multi-label NLP experiments.

Batch controls:
- Primary category for this batch: [INSERT CATEGORY]
- Number of emails: [INSERT COUNT]
- Batch prefix: [INSERT PREFIX]
- Split tag: [train | val | test | challenge_test]
- Module pool: KV6003 (Computing Project), KV5002 (Software Engineering), KV4006 (Databases)

Allowed labels:
- assessment: assignments, deadlines, submission, resits, marking policy
- timetabling: lecture/seminar time, room changes, clashes, cancellations
- resources: slides, recordings, reading lists, software/license access, links
- admin: enrolment, registration, student records, portal issues
- extenuating_circumstances: illness/personal issues, mitigation, extension requests
- feedback: feedback requests, mark breakdown, remarks/appeals

Generation rules:
- Every email must have at least 1 valid label.
- Around 20-35% of rows should be multi-intent (2 labels). Up to 5% may have 3 labels.
- Include linguistic variation:
	- formal/professional
	- casual text-speak (u, pls, thx)
	- typo-heavy or grammar-poor
	- concise one-liners
	- long rambling emails
- Include varied student tone: polite, anxious, confused, frustrated, apologetic, urgent.
- Include realistic university details: weeks, assignment IDs, submission portals, resit windows.
- Keep UK university context and wording style.

Difficulty controls (must be present in each batch):
- At least 15% ambiguous wording (intent not explicit in first sentence).
- At least 15% hard negatives (surface words from another class but true label is different).
- At least 10% near-duplicates, but vary wording enough for realism.

Duplicate policy for leakage control:
- Assign a duplicate_cluster_id.
- If a row is unique, use "none".
- Near-duplicates should share the same duplicate_cluster_id.
- Do not reuse duplicate clusters across different split tags.

Priority guidance:
- high: urgent/time-sensitive (deadline today, illness near deadline, exam issue)
- medium: needs reply soon but not critical
- low: informational or routine query

Output requirements:
- Output ONLY CSV rows (no markdown table, no code fence, no extra commentary).
- Columns and order must be exactly:
	email_id,subject,body,labels,module,priority,multi_intent,split_tag,duplicate_cluster_id,style_tag,noise_tag

Column definitions:
- email_id: [BATCH_PREFIX]_001 style IDs
- labels: pipe-separated label names, lowercase (example: assessment|resources)
- module: one module code from pool
- multi_intent: true/false
- split_tag: exactly the provided split tag
- duplicate_cluster_id: none or dup_xxx
- style_tag: formal | casual | typo_heavy | terse | rambling
- noise_tag: none | typo | slang | punctuation | mixed

Hard validation checklist (self-check before final output):
- Labels are from allowed set only.
- multi_intent=true iff labels column contains 2+ labels.
- No empty subject/body.
- At least 5 words in body for terse rows; at least 40 words for rambling rows.
- No placeholders like [INSERT], lorem ipsum, or template artifacts.
- Email text should not be identical across rows unless intentionally duplicated via duplicate_cluster_id.

